cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.DL, cs.HC. 

This paper discusses the development of a computer-assisted translation tool for Wikipedia articles, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques (cs.CL). The tool is designed to improve the quality and quantity of articles in different languages, which relates to information retrieval and cross-lingual information processing (cs.IR). The tool is also intended for use by an open community, which involves human-computer interaction and social computing (cs.CY, cs.HC). Finally, the tool uses machine learning and deep learning techniques to adapt to the specific needs of Wikipedia content, which relates to deep learning (cs.DL).
